						               													<description>With this adventure booklet you can experience another exciting adventure of Robin Hood and his companions. It plays around the same time as chapter 4. The story of the adventure plays independently of the others and therefore no prior knowledge of other chapters is necessary. Since new elements and tiles from later adventures have been added, it is recommended that you have already played the basic game. All outlaws already have their own special abilities. The functions for new items can be found on the following page. No prior knowledge of this adventure is required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A boy arrived at the secret camp crying with a rabbit in his arms and searched for Robin Hood, screaming loudly. &amp;quot;Help! Rooobinnnn!&amp;rdquo; he yelled! &amp;quot;You have to help me! My rabbit suddenly lay down motionless on the forest floor!&amp;rdquo; he sobbed. The child cried, yes he wanted to say something in a hurry: &amp;quot;Oh, but... but it's not just my rabbit so bad. The animals, plants and people feel bad. The animals are lying around, the plants cannot grow and the people suffer Headaches and are powerless.&amp;quot; Robin immediately picked up his bow, rounded up his friends and them decided to look around the forest and ask the people involved what happened.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
